                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d677">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">611.1731/189: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Nicaragua</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Lane</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Managua</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-03-07T14:00:00-06:00"
                            >March 7, 1936—2 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received March 7—4:55 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>57. Department’s 29, March 6, 3 p.m. Information regarding Costa Rican and
                    Guatemalan negotiations apparently impressed favorably Nicaragua’s this morning.
                    Will telegraph further after afternoon session.</p>
                <p>Have decided to leave March 14 and have so advised Mr. Long who will presumably
                    arrive March 16.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lane</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
